strixnoapi extends upstream strix in three ways:

  1. A local OAuth-backed HTTP proxy (strixnoapi/proxy/) that routes LLM calls through
     subscription CLI credentials (Claude Code, OpenAI Codex, Google Gemini, Cursor)
     instead of billed API keys. Strix's agent loop, prompt templates, skills system,
     sandbox, tools, and vulnerability taxonomy are unchanged.

  2. Security hardening (strixnoapi/security/, containers/Dockerfile.sandbox,
     containers/seccomp.json) above upstream's baseline: cap-drop ALL, read-only
     container root, custom seccomp profile, PID and memory caps, egress allowlist,
     hash-chained audit log, curated secret-pattern redaction.

  3. UX and reliability upgrades (strixnoapi/interface/, strixnoapi/checkpoint/,
     strixnoapi/report/): interactive setup, doctor diagnostics, resume-from-checkpoint,
     SARIF / HTML / PDF report exports.

Upstream remains authoritative for scan behavior. Upstream security patches are
tracked via the `upstream` git remote and are cherry-pickable into strixnoapi with
minimal friction.

For the upstream project, see https://github.com/usestrix/strix.
